1 olive oil
1 packet pine nuts
½ head broccoli
½ pear
1 bag herbs
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle balsamic glaze
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Heat a medium frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast pine nuts tossing,
until golden, 3-4 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• Roughly chop broccoli (see ingredients) including stalk.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook
broccoli with a dash of water, tossing, until just tender, 6-7 minutes.

• While the broccoli is cooking, thinly slice pear (see ingredients). Pick and
thinly slice herbs.

• In a large bowl, add a drizzle of olive oil and a generous pinch of salt and
pepper. Add salad leaves, pear, broccoli, grated Parmesan cheese and
herbs. Toss to coat.

TIP: Make the salad in a serving bowl to save on washing up!

• Transfer pear and broccoli salad to a serving dish.
• Sprinkle with toasted pine nuts and drizzle with some balsamic glaze to
serve. Enjoy!